%N A048783 Numbers k such that prime(k) - sigma(k) - phi(k) = prime(k+1) - sigma(k+1) - phi(k+1), where sigma(k) = sum of divisors of k.
%H A048783 Amiram Eldar, <a href="/A048783/b048783.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%o A048783 (PARI) isok(n) = (prime(n) - sigma(n) - eulerphi(n) == prime(n+1) - sigma(n+1) - eulerphi(n+1)) \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jul 14 2013
%o A048783 (PARI) list(lim) = {my(v1 = -1, k = 0, f); forprime(p = 1, lim, k++; f = factor(k); v2 = p - sigma(f) - eulerphi(f); if(v2 == v1, print1(k-1, ", ")); v1 = v2);} \\ _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 06 2026
